			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				Look, there is nothing there that one can't glean from common sense.
<br />

<br />
Humanity evolves. Evolution is change, chaos, pain, destruction, and rebirth... and then the cycle begins again. Therefore, at some point in the future, all hell will break loose. You don't need a prophecy to know that mankind is going to have a turbulent future the likes of which we can barely imagine. 
<br />

<br />
If you want to be worried about the future, worry about it because of the picture our current science can paint for you, rather than something in a moldy holy book. Those books have no value whatsoever beyond morality, and the time will come where they will have outlived their usefulness.
<br />

<br />
If you take your eyes off the ground and have the will to look at the horizon, <a href="http://www.kurzweilai.net/articles/art0134.html?m=1" target="_blank" class="postlink">this is the kind of thing you may see.</a> Every bit as prophetic, beautiful and terrifying as anything in a holy book, but this has the benefit of hard science to back it up rather than flimsy, factless prophecy. Prophecy only has meaning if you consider time-travel to be possible.
<br />

<br />
Everything comes down to whether or not you believe humanity, at some point in the future, will get it right or not. If we can get it right just one time, it pays for the whole bloody affair.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
			</td></tr>
		</table>
		</td>
