				<div class="postbody">
				Still reading that article.. the part about how someday it will be possible for us to download our brains into a databank and live on in a robot's body, was really interesting. Sounds like, if we reach that point without blowing the world up, we'll be creating our own evolution. Or that our mind brought upon this evolution.
<br />

<br />
It does seem to scare me though, being able to live forever in your mind.. yet kind of exhilarating. It would become almost impossible to completely die. It would make me wonder if there were really a heaven, and if their weren't, what about the people who just died and became nothingness. We'd possibly be cheating out the natural process of life.
<br />

<br />
I think it would be hard to hault our evolution of technology even with a nuclear war(althought it would undoubtedly slow down). Some of us would most likely survive, and since more and more data is becoming digital, it would be easier to keep the growth alive.
<br />

<br />
All of this talk of this type of technology really makes you think something like the Matrix is possible heh.. albeit much farther down the road when computers gain the ability to think for themselves. It really scares me...<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
