Raviel, as to your remarks about stuff like cracking the human genome, they have been working on that for well over ten years  Heck, I bet one of the first things that Watson and Crick (the 'discoverers' of DNA) was that it needs to be decoded and that was a bit over 50 years ago.
<br />

<br />
Also, I think he is taking his exponential growth too linerarly, if that makes sense.  I think he is depending on the linear continuation of the exponential increase.  History, though, shows us that is not always the case.  Fall of the Roman Empire, the dark ages, repressive Catholic church, revitilization of the rennaisance, persecution of new thinkers (Gailelo), industrial revolution, word wars, etcetera.
<br />

<br />
My point is that I think the actual historical evidence shows us that there is exponential growth, then it stagnates then we hit another moment of exponential growth; rinse and repeat.
<br />

<br />
Raviel to touch on what you mentioned, a perfect example in the modern world are these undeveloped countries that we have.  We are going to evolve as a species, but eventually everybody in the world will be held back due to the less developed parts of the world; growth will stagnate.  When those countries/civilizations get 'caught up' then we again will evolve.
<br />

<br />
Also I feel that you do not give the everday Joe Blow enough credit.  Like it or not, the fact is that masses rule the world:  masses = joe blow.  There are, obviously, the thinkers and leaders but they are only as good as the Joe Blows.
<br />
Maybe Joe Blow does not know the math behind a linear curve or an exponential curve or a cubic one.  However you draw them out, then I bet just about anybody can look at that and tell you what is going on.
<br />
You do not need to know the quadratic calculation thing to interpet what you see.<br />
